# LucidGate example list: downloadmanager
# Format: Three fields per line: banned|exception ext|mime value. This combines extension and MIME download policy in one file.
# Lines beginning with # are comments and are ignored by the loader.
# To activate a rule, copy one example, remove the leading # and adapt it to your environment.
# You can include another file with: .Include<relative-or-absolute-path>
#
# Commented examples:
# banned ext .exe
# banned ext .dll
# banned ext .msi
# banned ext .scr
# banned mime application/x-msdownload
# banned mime application/x-dosexec
# exception ext .txt
# exception ext .pdf
# exception mime application/pdf
# exception mime image/png
